            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/doom-running-on-pdf-weird-port-id-software-fps-pc-mod-1851739634<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><figure id="" data-id="6bf79c95aef2f9a78f360aad9d8785e9" data-recommend-id="image://6bf79c95aef2f9a78f360aad9d8785e9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="A screenshot of PDF Doom with the Doomguy's face pasted on it. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot of PDF Doom with the Doomguy's face pasted on it. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->id Software / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6bf79c95aef2f9a78f360aad9d8785e9" data-recommend-id="image://6bf79c95aef2f9a78f360aad9d8785e9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="A screenshot of PDF Doom with the Doomguy's face pasted on it. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>A crafty high-schooler was able to do something I didn’t think was possible: They got <em>Doom </em>running inside a PDF file. Seriously. And weirdly, it works better than you might expect! </p><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><div data-video-id="196049" data-monetizable="true" data-position="sidebar" data-video-title="This Modern Warfare 3 Gameplay Feature Spices Up A Weak Campaign" data-video-blog-id="9" data-video-network="kotaku" data-video-duration="134" data-playlist="196049,196163,195697" data-current="196049"><div><p>This Modern Warfare 3 Gameplay Feature Spices Up A Weak Campaign</p></div><video disablepictureinpicture="" muted="" playsinline="" width="100%" height="100%" crossorigin="anonymous" preload="none"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196049/196049_240p.mp4" label="240p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196049/196049_480p.mp4" label="480p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196049/196049_720p.mp4" label="720p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196049/196049_1080p.mp4" label="1080p" type="video/mp4"><track kind="captions" label="English" src="https://kinja.com/api/videoupload/caption/21580.vtt" srclang="en"></video><div><ul><li data-label="">Off</li><li data-label="English">English</li></ul></div></div><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><p> Over the last two decades, getting id Software’s 1993 classic FPS <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/a-doom-mod-where-you-make-friends-with-demons-1825445400?_gl=1*340tb7*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMDgyNDIwMi4xMS4xLjE3MzA4MzEwMzcuMzMuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/a-doom-mod-where-you-make-friends-with-demons-1825445400?_gl=1*340tb7*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMDgyNDIwMi4xMS4xLjE3MzA4MzEwMzcuMzMuMC4w"><em>Doom</em></a></span><em>&nbsp;</em>to run on devices that were never intended to play games has become a popular hobby among modders and tinkerers. In the last few years alone, we’ve seen <em>Doom</em> ported to <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/doom-weirdest-ports-keyboard-atm-calculator-tractor-pc-1850726374&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/doom-weirdest-ports-keyboard-atm-calculator-tractor-pc-1850726374">tractors, ATMs, pregnancy tests</a></span>, and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/you-can-now-play-doom-via-twitter-1847881209?_gl=1*1t7785b*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMDgyNDIwMi4xMS4xLjE3MzA4MzAyNDYuNjAuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/you-can-now-play-doom-via-twitter-1847881209?_gl=1*1t7785b*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMDgyNDIwMi4xMS4xLjE3MzA4MzAyNDYuNjAuMC4w">even on Twitter via tweets</a></span>. And now, you can add PDF files to the list of “<span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/doom-alarmo-nintendo-alarm-clock-hack-modder-usb-id-pc-1851690005?_gl=1*jumrnh*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNjg4ODU0Mi4yNzkuMS4xNzM2ODg4ODIyLjQ3LjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/doom-alarmo-nintendo-alarm-clock-hack-modder-usb-id-pc-1851690005?_gl=1*jumrnh*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNjg4ODU0Mi4yNzkuMS4xNzM2ODg4ODIyLjQ3LjAuMA..">Things That You Can Play <em>Doom</em> On.</a></span>” </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.ign.com/articles/move-over-toasters-doom-is-now-playable-inside-a-pdf&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.ign.com/articles/move-over-toasters-doom-is-now-playable-inside-a-pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">As spotted by <em>IGN</em></a></span>, Github user and self described “high school student” Ading2210 has created a small website that lets you play a PDF version of <em>Doom</em>. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://doompdf.pages.dev/doom.pdf&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://doompdf.pages.dev/doom.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Click here to play <em>Doom </em>in a PDF</a></span>. (Note that it only works in Chromium browsers.)</p><p>Here’s a video of this new PDF port of <em>Doom </em>in action: </p><p>How is this possible, you might ask? Aren’t PDF files just static images or text? Surprisingly, that’s not exactly true. According to Ading2210, PDF files support JavaScript, and this is used by most modern browsers to display PDFs.  Adding2210 took advantage of this and used ASCII characters to create the visuals you see when playing <em>Doom</em>’s PDF port. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://github.com/ading2210/doompdf&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://github.com/ading2210/doompdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">You can read the full descirption of how this was all achieved over on the Github page</a></span>. It’s very impressive.</p><p>Now you might be wondering: Why is <em>Doom </em>so easy to port? Well, that’s because <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/so-called-pirates-are-doing-the-work-when-publishers-fa-1846533244?_gl=1*sos5qp*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNjg4ODU0Mi4yNzkuMS4xNzM2ODg4ODIyLjQ3LjAuMA..#:~:text=This%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a,with%20a%20screen.&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/so-called-pirates-are-doing-the-work-when-publishers-fa-1846533244?_gl=1*sos5qp*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNjg4ODU0Mi4yNzkuMS4xNzM2ODg4ODIyLjQ3LjAuMA..#:~:text=This%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a,with%20a%20screen.">Id Software released <em>Doom</em>’s source code in 1997</a></span>—just four years after the game’s explosive debut. Since then, fans have spent the past 25+ years creating “source ports” of the shooter that both extend the game in countless ways and let you play it on practically anything. </p><p>Can you imagine, in 2025, a video game company releasing a hugely popular game’s source code a few years after launch? It’s wild to think about. But thanks to that source code release decades ago, fans have been able to port <em>Doom </em>to basically anything. I can’t wait to see what the next weird port of <em>Doom </em>looks like. </p><p> .<br></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
